# Command Center & Notification Engine (Phase 26)

Read **[COMMAND_CENTER.md](../../COMMAND_CENTER.md)** before changes to Command Center, executive feed, quick actions, or notification distribution.

## Layer ownership (mandatory before implementation)

| Surface | Owner |
|---------|-------|
| Command Center UI | **Customer App** (`/app/command-center`) |
| Notification Engine | **Shared** (`lib/notification/`) |
| Event delivery APIs | **Shared** (`/api/presence/*`) |
| Unonight pilot metrics | **Platform Admin** |

## Rules

1. **One Aipify** — Web, Desktop, Mobile consume the same `get_command_center_bundle()` / notification tables
2. Never duplicate business logic in desktop or mobile clients — lightweight clients only
3. Notification Engine distributes Core events; it does not re-implement Intelligence, Action, or License logic
4. Executive feed uses professional tone (`lib/presence/personality.ts`)
5. Quick actions reduce context switching — server-side via `perform_presence_quick_action`
6. Track engagement in `presence_engagement_events` to prevent alert fatigue
7. Plan packaging enforced server-side (`capabilities` in bundle) — see `lib/notification/packaging.ts`
8. Native desktop client lives in `apps/command-center/` (Phase 27) — see `desktop-command-center.mdc`; mobile not yet built
9. `/app/presence` redirects to `/app/command-center`

> Desktop is another window into Aipify Core — not a separate product.
